> now we got this and after checking About us and Contact i didn't find anything useful in these pages but i found something intersting in Contact source!

![contact](https://k.top4top.io/p_1809yh84v1.png)

contact us source code has a comment at end of the page which seems like it's a directory.

![/](https://e.top4top.io/p_18093yudv1.png)

yes it's a directory and also i found a very long base64 text in the page source, i tried to decode it manually but it was encoded multiple times , tried to decode the result multiple times but still produce another base64 text, it is multi cyclic encoding and it was encoded 25 times so i wrote this python script to automate the process of decoding.

```python
import base64
text = ""
for i in range(25):
    text = base64.b64decode(text)
print("[+] Text Is : " ,text)
```
and the result is 
![img](https://g.top4top.io/p_180906nz91.png)

now we only have the password B100dyPa$$w0rd

> since we have the password only i continued checking the webpages to maybe find something intersting again

* view parameter takes the name of a file and include it in the web page so i tested for lfi and read /etc/passwd and it worked and we got user "john"

```bash
?view=../../../../../../../../etc/passwd
```
